text: Location for Advanced Remanufacturing Technology Centre ( ARTC). This is part of A*STAR the research wing of Government of Singapore. ARTC focuses on Engineering research. Areas such as Robotics, 3D printing, Artificial Intelligence, Digitalisation, Supply Chain 4.0 & Hyper Personalisation for FMCG. Plenty of parking in the basement. Walking distance from the 199 bus stop. There are private buses too that pick up & drop to MRT stations at fixed morning & evening hours. The closest point for Lunch is atleast 20 min walk, though bus service is available.
Easy access, sufficient car parking lots but parking fee display have been failed sine beginning of year 2021 till now. Don't understand why such building also collects parking fee.
Unless you work here or had to visit for other reasons, there is nothing here for you. There isn't any food court or cafeteria at this location.
a part of Jurong Innovationn  District where technologes and natures meet a real clean tech
